Here you are multiplying `freq` by your *character*, which creates a garbage number, and then adding that garbage number to your String one time:

    res+=(freq*hm1.get(str));

You need to add the character to your String `freq` times, so you need a loop:

    char c = hm1.get(str);
    for (int i=0; i&lt;freq; i++) {
        res += c;
    }

Or if you&#39;re using Java 11 or later, there is convenience method for String to repeat it:

    res += String.valueOf(hm1.get(str)).repeat(freq);

The problem is in this line: `res+=(freq*hm1.get(str));`. It is multiplying the frequency with the ASCII value of the character, not repeating the character `freq` times. This would work in Python but not in Java. You should change this line to repeat the character `freq` times. Below is example fix to your code:

    for(String str:arr){
        if(hm2.containsKey(str)){
            freq=hm2.get(str);
        }else{
            for(int i=0;i&lt;freq;i++){
                res+=hm1.get(str);
            }
            freq=1;
        }
    }

