To print English numbers you should change a `Locale`. But you only print em in the `&lt;s:iterator&gt;` tag. You should know how to get a current [`Locale`][2] from the [`ActionContext`][1] in JSP. 

Then you save a current locale to the variable before you change it
```xml
&lt;s:set var = &quot;old_locale&quot; value = &quot;%{#context.locale}&quot; /&gt;

&lt;!-- then change a current locale --&gt;

&lt;s:set var = &quot;%{#context.locale}&quot; value = &quot;%{new java.util.Locale(&quot;en&quot;, &quot;US&quot;)&quot; /&gt;

&lt;!-- print numbers with a new locale --&gt;

&lt;s:iterator begin=&quot;1&quot; end=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
    &lt;s:property value=&quot;top&quot;/&gt;,
&lt;/s:iterator&gt;

&lt;!-- then return a current locale back --&gt;

&lt;s:set var = &quot;%{#context.locale}&quot; value = &quot;%{#old_locale}&quot; /&gt;
```

  [1]: https://struts.apache.org/maven/struts2-core/apidocs/com/opensymphony/xwork2/ActionContext.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Locale.html

